Class MorseDecoder

java.lang.Object
model.MorseDecoder
public class MorseDecoder extends Object
This class is intended to take morse code and convert it to readable English.

    • letterPositioning

      public void letterPositioning(BinaryTree<Character> passingTree, char letter, String symbol)
      Method decides where to place the letter in binary tree If it is a dot it goes to the left, else if it is a dash it goes to the right
      Parameters:
      passingTree - the subtree that will be used to decide where the letter goes
      letter - the alphabetic representation of morse code
      symbol - the morse code This code is from Tutorial_11_16 but has been modified to correctly make Binary Morse Tree
